<h2><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-hand-up"></i>&nbsp;User Input</h2>

<div style="padding-top: 20px">
  <div class="panel panel-info">
    <div class="panel-heading">
      <h3 class="panel-title"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-info-sign"></i>&nbsp;User Input has been merged into the scan pipeline</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="panel-body">
      <p>
        Starting with <strong>v5.3.17</strong>, document and IOC submission is integrated
        directly into the scan pipeline.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Documents</strong> — use the <em>"Attach Documents"</em> field on the
            <a href="${docroot}/newscan">New Scan</a> form.  Files are processed by
            Apache Tika and IOCs feed into the scan.</li>
        <li><strong>IOCs / targets</strong> — paste them as the scan target or use the
            batch target feature in the API.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>The standalone user-input service has been retired.</p>
      <a href="${docroot}/newscan" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">
        <i class="glyphicon glyphicon-screenshot"></i>&nbsp;Go to New Scan
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

